                    <comment id="12379271" author="ericv@kinzan.com" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2002 07:28:58 +0100"  >you might also want it to be byte oriented either OutputStream or byte[]. For instance pushing xml &lt;br/&gt;
payload ala SOAP requires byte not String request body. I handled this case by extending &lt;br/&gt;
PostMethod and adding a setBody( byte[] ) and rewrote writeRequestBody which defers to the &lt;br/&gt;
parent when body hasn&amp;#39;t been set.</comment>
                    <comment id="12379272" author="rwaldhof@us.britannica.com" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2002 22:47:10 +0100"  >I just added a setRequestBody(String) method to PostMethod.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If someone wants to work on a streaming or file based form, have at it, but you &lt;br/&gt;
may want to consider using PutMethod as the base instead.</comment>
